                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Written in a fine handwriting</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1400" to="1499"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <desc>
                          Old palaeographical features: 
                          the upper parts of ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, and ጸ are of triangular shape; 
                          ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order sometimes attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line; 
                          ዐ and ፀ are rounded; 
                          ኖ has the loop marking the 7th order of angular shape (e.g., on <locus target="#29ra4"/>, <locus target="#140ra3"/>); 
                          has a loop on the right side.
                      </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Titles, nomina sacra.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3v"/>
                        <desc>Drawing of the Virgin Mary with the Christ Child and the angels, outlined in black. The faces and the hands of the Virgin Mary and the 
                           Christ Child are coloured in red.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="band" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#4r"/>
                        <desc>Ornamental band, coloured in yellow and red, with two human heads.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="band" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#108r"/>
                        <desc>Ornamental band, outlined in black and coloured in yellow and red.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                   </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="StampExlibris">Stamp</desc>
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <note>Seal of the <ref type="ins" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0303BNF">Bibliothèque Nationale de France</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="MagicText">Two magical prayers</desc>
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <note>
                              The prayers are barely legible due to faded ink. The former is against the diseases of the body parts, the latter concerns the number 77.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc type="Excerpt">Prayers of the Eucharist</desc>
                           <locus target="#1v"/>
                           <note>
                              Prayers are taken from the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3120Anapho">Anaphora of John Chrysostom</ref>; text edited in 
                              <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/TQ2NBVAC"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia"/><title level="m">Chrestomathia Aethiopica edita et glossario explanata</title><editor><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Christian Friedrich August</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Dillmann</t:surname></editor><pubPlace>Lipsiae</pubPlace><publisher>T. O. Weigel</publisher><date>1866</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_V2XoxZmczckC</note><citedRange unit="page">55 l. 12 - 56</citedRange></bibl>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc type="Excerpt">Prayers of the Eucharist</desc>
                           <locus target="#2v"/>
                           <note>
                              The prayers are taken from an unidentified anaphora. The text begins as follows: 
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ይብል፡ ካህን፡ ሥጋሁ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወክቡር፡ ማሕየዊ፡ ዘበአማን፡ ዘእግዚእነ፡ ወመድኀኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘይትወሀብ፡ ለስርየተ፡ ኃጢአት፡ ወለሕይወት፡ ዘለዓለም፡ ለእለ፡ 
                           ይንሥኡ፡ እምኔሁ፡ ዘበአማን፡ አሜን፨</q>
                              <q xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ ውእቱ፡ ዘሎቱ፡ ይደሉ፡ ክብር፡ ወስብሐት፡ ወሰጊድ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፨</q>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc type="AcquisitionNote"/>
                           <locus target="#158v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አጥረዮ፡ <gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="9"/> በእንተ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ 
                              <add place="inline">
                                 <supplied reason="omitted">ኀይለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</supplied>
                              </add>
                           </q>
                           <note>
                              The note is partly illegible and partly covered by a seal of the Vatican Library. It mentions <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11511WaldaMa">Walda Māryam</persName> 
                              and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11512HaylaGi">Ḫayla Giyorgis</persName>, whose nome is overwritten.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <desc type="StampExlibris">Stamp</desc>
                           <locus target="#158v"/>
                           <note>Seal of the <ref type="ins" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0303BNF">Bibliothèque Nationale de France</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 67 | Aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of arms of pope 
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7893PiusIX">Pius IX</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>The previous shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Cod. 9 Petri Valle</q> and the title of the book <q xml:lang="la">Liturgia Aethiopica</q> 
                              are erased.
                           </desc>
                        </item>
